  "closed_reason" : "Duplicate",
  "title" : "How to including variables within strings?",
  "body" : "<p>So, we all should know that you can include variables into strings by doing:</p>\n<pre><code>String string = &quot;A string &quot; + aVariable;\n</code></pre>\n<p>Is there a way to do it like:</p>\n<pre><code>String string = &quot;A string {aVariable}&quot;;\n</code></pre>\n<p><em>In other words:</em> Without having to close the quotation marks and adding plus signs. It's very unattractive.</p>\n"
